text.tspan: MapServer is an Open Source platform for publishing
spatial data and interactive mapping applications to
the web. Originally developed in the mid-1990’s at the
University of Minnesota, MapServer is released under
an MIT-style license, and runs on all major platforms.
It is written in C and it is maintained by a growing
number of developers from around the world.
It is supported by a diverse group of organizations
that fund enhancements and maintenance, and
administered within OSGeo by the MapServer Project
Steering Committee made up of developers and other
